<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-08-14T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-08-14T03:00:00-05:00" n="454" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d454">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/9361: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-14T17:00:00+09:00">August 14, 1937—5
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received August 14—9:37 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>268. Embassy’s 263, August 13, 7 p.m., paragraph 3. The French
                                Ambassador who was summoned last evening to an interview with the
                                Vice Minister for Foreign Affairs<note n="4" xml:id="d454fn4">K.
                                    Horinouchi.</note> (see our 264, August 13, 11 p.m., paragraph
                                4) did not take that opportunity to support the representations of
                                the five Ambassadors in Nanking because he felt such action to be
                                superfluous in the face of the Vice Minister’s statement.<note n="5" xml:id="d454fn5">The German Embassy also did not participate in
                                    any collective <hi rend="italic">démarche</hi>.</note></p>
                            <p>Repeated to Nanking.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>